Time Complexity:

Let n = size of array

    Outer loop → O(n)
    Inner loop → O(n)

Overall: O(n²)


Space Complexity:

    In-place sorting (no extra space)

Overall: O(1)


Approach:

1. Traverse array using index i from 0 to n-1

2. Assume current index i as minimum

3. Traverse remaining array (j = i+1 to n-1):
   - Find index of smallest element

4. Swap:
   - nums[i] with nums[min]

5. Repeat for all positions

6. Array gets sorted in ascending order





class Solution {
    public void sortColors(int[] nums) {
        for (int i = 0; i < nums.length; i++) {
            int min = i;
            for (int j = i + 1; j < nums.length; j++) {
                if (nums[min] > nums[j]) {
                    min = j;
                }
            }
            int temp = nums[min];
            nums[min] = nums[i];
            nums[i] = temp;
        }
    }
}
